 ('3', '16', 'en_gb', 'PSHE', 'PSHE', '<p>I am experienced at delivering PSHE lessons on a range of topics, including mental health & well-being; sex & relationships.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'red', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'row1', NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2015-09-01 20:05:47', '2016-05-10 19:35:03', 'fb2ffe34-ed9f-4059-9371-7f7f50424369'),
 ('4', '23', 'en_gb', 'Health', 'Health', '<p>I worked as a Senior Sexual Health Promotion Practitioner for the NHS in Brighton & Hove for 12 years</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'blue', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'row1', NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2015-12-01 19:47:40', '2016-05-10 19:35:03', '9e26468b-51ee-4b2b-9e87-14eefeff5118'),
 ('5', '26', 'en_gb', 'Youth Work', 'youthwork', '<p>Liz Dean Consultancy has teamed up with Laura Clark, a very experienced Sex Educator to advocate for the sex and relationship rights of people with learning disabilities</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'blue', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'row2', NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2015-12-01 20:00:40', '2016-05-10 19:35:03', '6e934f04-7f98-445c-afac-e40b2ec9665e'),
 ('6', '28', 'en_gb', 'Relationships', 'Relationships', '<p>I have recently been working on behalf of the Brighton & Hove Healthy Schools Team and I have developed a teaching pack covering the impact and influence of the media and pornography on young people\'s sexualisation</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'red', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'row2', NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2015-12-01 20:01:43', '2016-05-10 19:35:03', '650d0348-75d7-4190-b2c4-375afb4b3ed9'),
 ('7', '30', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>I have been an Associate Trainer for the FPA for the past 6 years.&nbsp; I developed and deliver a one&nbsp; day course \'<em>Fantasy Vs Reality: the impact and influence of pornography on young people\'s sexual attitudes and behaviour</em>\'.&nbsp; I have also co-written and deliver \'<em>T</em><em>he Pleasure Principle</em>\' and \'<em>Young people, sex and alcohol\'</em>&nbsp;for the FPA. &nbsp;If you are interested in booking on these courses, visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.fpa.org.uk/\">www.fpa.org.uk/training</a></p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, '.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2015-12-07 01:35:07', '2016-05-10 19:35:03', '318dbc6e-a0ff-499d-9f53-47266244c824'),
 ('19', '54', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<p>As well as my extensive work with practitioners, I also work directly with young people, delivering lessons, workshops and 1-1 sessions. &nbsp;I currently work with The Young People\'s Centre in Brighton and the wider Youth Collective <a href=\"http://www.brightonandhoveyouthcollective.org.uk\">www.brightonandhoveyouthcollective.org.uk</a> &nbsp;This is important to me to ensure my training courses are kept in line with current practice (I also love this work :)</p>', '', '<p>My background is in the NHS, education and youth work.&nbsp; I have a BA (Hons)in Education and MA in Health Promotion.&nbsp; I currently work on a freelance basis developing and providing high quality training, developing educational resources and conducting needs assessments and small scale research. I also directly deliver lessons and workshops to young people in schools, colleges and youth settings.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2016-02-24 02:23:52', '2016-05-10 19:35:03', '191bcf33-cec3-477a-9d2a-e5a2045e3efe'),
 ('20', '55', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>I am experienced at delivering PSHE lessons on a range of topics, including mental health & well-being; sex & relationships; the impact and influence of pornography; the media & sexualisation; anti-bullying; stress management; nutrition; physical activity; sexuality/challenging homophobia as well as money management. I can deliver one off lessons, a series of lessons, organise a PSHE day team delivery with a trusted team of colleagues or present at assemblies. Please contact me to discuss your requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I work to up to date good practice and guidance on PSHE delivery in association with (links to PSHE Association / Sex Ed Forum etc)</p>', '', 'PSHE', NULL, NULL, 'PSHE', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2016-02-24 19:04:52', '2016-04-21 23:43:18', 'd4232ede-1492-4111-9b2b-a79ee9e93e84'),
 ('21', '56', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img src=\"{asset:11:url}\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am a self-employed educator, trainer, youth worker and facilitator. I have 15 years experience of working across a variety of areas and subjects including Public Health & Health Promotion; Behaviour Change; Motivational Interviewing; Youth work, Education and Social care covering a range of issues relating to health & well-being, specifically sexual health; drugs & alcohol and mental health and well-being. I plan and deliver presentations, training courses, workshops and lessons. I also produce teaching resources and health promotion materials, conduct needs assessments and small scale pieces of research. I am based in Sussex, but also work across the UK.<br><br>I am a member of MINT (Motivational Interviewing Network of Trainers) <a href=\"http://www.motivationalinterviewing.org\">www.motivationalinterviewing.o...</a><br><br>As well as my extensive work with practitioners, I also work directly with young people, delivering lessons, workshops and 1-1 sessions. I currently work with The Young People\'s Centre in Brighton and the wider Youth Collective <a href=\"http://www.brightonandhoveyouthcollective.org.uk\">www.brightonandhoveyouthcollec...</a> This is important to me to ensure my training courses are kept in line with current practice and the challenges and possibilities in this work.<br><br>My background is in the NHS, education and youth work. I have a BA (Hons) in Education and MA in Health Promotion. I currently work on a self-employed basis developing and providing high quality training, developing educational resources and conducting needs assessments and small scale research. I also directly deliver lessons and workshops to young people in schools, colleges and youth settings.I have been an Associate Trainer for the FPA for the past 8 years. I developed and deliver a one day course \'Fantasy Vs Reality: the impact and influence of pornography on young people\'s sexual attitudes and behaviour\'. I have also co-written and deliver \'The Pleasure Principle\' and \'Young people, sex and alcohol\' for the FPA. If you are interested in booking on these courses, visit <a href=\"http://www.fpa.org.uk/training\">www.fpa.org.uk/training<br></a></p>', '', 'About', NULL, NULL, 'About', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-24 19:23:30', '2016-05-17 20:07:07', '224250c6-c8ac-40be-8cab-b2e7d2565b57'),
 ('22', '57', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Course participant, Brighton, March 2014', '<p>\'<em>Great session! Very knowledgeable trainer!\'</em></p>', 'FVR, London, 2013', '<p><em>\'Liz provided a very interesting and engaging session and I now feel more confident in delivering my sex and relationships work, especially in tackling issues relating to pornography</em>\'<br></p>', NULL, 'textRow1', NULL, NULL, '2016-02-24 19:25:02', '2016-05-17 20:07:08', '34d5bf17-2abb-434b-8059-92015ca5c6b3'),
 ('23', '58', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FVR, Dorset, Sept 2012', '<p><em>\'An excellent course which was well presented and interactive\'</em><br></p>', 'FVR, London 2012', '<p><em>\'Liz was clearly very knowledgeable and created a safe, boundaried environment to explore the issues within\'</em></p>', NULL, 'textRow1', NULL, NULL, '2016-02-24 19:31:46', '2016-05-17 20:07:08', 'cb9f67a9-b832-4676-8749-f45b31d5a785'),
 ('24', '59', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liz Dean Consultancy has teamed up with Laura Clark, a very experienced Sex Educator to advocate for the sex and relationship rights of people with learning disabilities.&nbsp;&nbsp; This is often a sensitive challenging area yet fundamental to ensuring positive health and well being.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We can offer training to staff on the following areas in relation to learning disability; sex and the law; capacity and consent and translating policy into practice.&nbsp; We aim to build staffs confidence and competence in addressing and responding to issues arising in a practical way  such as public vs. private behaviour; appropriate touching, developing and maintaining healthy personal relationships, sexualisation and issues relating to pornography, talking about personal relationships and sexuality (PRS) with your clients, contraception needs, STIs, sexual health, and sexual orientation.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Our work in Sussex includes delivering training to staff at St Johns School and College; Barnados; Cherish Youth Club; YMCA; Extratime and the Community Learning Disability Team.&nbsp; We can offer bespoke training sessions to suit your requirements.&nbsp; We would build in consulting with staff beforehand to ascertain needs arising and current examples of practice relevant to training.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We can also support the delivery of PRS education on the above issues in a style that is accessible to your residents using current evidence based high quality resources. Contact us for more information.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\">Pornography courses: </strong>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Visit the FPA for further details and information on how to book : <a href=\"http://www.fpa.org.uk\">www.fpa.org.uk</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>I am happy to be contacted for more information on my work in the area of pornography and its impact. I often work with the media in supporting the research into television documentaries in this area. For example: <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b040n2ph\">http://www.bbc.co.uk/programme...</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>These are some other examples of recent courses I have developed and delivered: </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\">Course 1:&nbsp; Teenage Pregnancy & Substance Misuse Training for Social Work Practitioners (1 day course)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\">Aim:&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br>To enable social work practitioners to gain more awareness, knowledge and confidence in tackling teenage pregnancy and substance misuse and have clarity regarding their role and responsibilities with Looked After Young People according to local and national guidance & good practice</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\">Objectives: </strong><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Understand the issues and needs of young people in relation to teenage pregnancy , substance misuse and being a young parent, with specific issues for Looked After Young People and vulnerable young people</li><li>Feel clear regarding your role and responsibility in the agenda and have improved confidence in making assessments, delivering interventions and in referring on.</li><li>Explore what can influence our interventions with young people and how we can achieve the most effective outcomes with the young person</li><li>To have an improved knowledge of the support services and referral routes in place for teenage pregnancy, young parents and substance misuse.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p><strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\">Course 2:Thrills, spills & pills: Sex, drugs, alcohol and young people. (1 day course)</strong><br>&nbsp;<br>Rationale<br>Increasingly practitioners working with young people are becoming aware that their alcohol use has direct links with their sexual activity. As well as enabling easier interaction on a social level alcohol use lowers inhibitions and sometimes causes young people to do things they would not do had they not been drinking. Regret features largely in young peoples description of sexual activity when they have been drinking. This course aims to look at young peoples alcohol consumption, risk taking, and how this is affected by alcohol, and the sexual activity that ensues. It also aims to support practitioners formulate strategies and interventions to work with young people around these issues.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aim The purpose of this course is to enhance participants understanding of key issues and links between sexual activity and alcohol use, to increase their confidence in addressing these issues with young people.<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><br>At the end of this course, participants will have:<br></p><ul><li>an understanding of current research and resources around young peoples sexual activity and alcohol use.increased awareness of the links between alcohol use and sexual activity</li><li>explored values and attitudes towards risk taking behaviour</li><li>gained practical tools to support their work with young people around alcohol use and sexual activity</li></ul><p><br><strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\">Course 3 R U Ready? Supporting Young People to consider their readiness for sexual relationships</strong><br>&nbsp;<br>Rationale Many young people continue to report high levels of regret associated with their first sexual experiences. The earlier young people have sex means they are less likely to be engaging in consensual sex and less likely to practice safer sex leaving them emotionally vulnerable and at risk of STIs or an unplanned pregnancy.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aim This course will explore the issues and pressures on young people to become sexually active and enable practitioners to be more confident in offering young people practical skills and strategies to delay sex until they are ready. These principles apply not only to first sex but to ongoing new sexual relationships.<br>&nbsp;<br><strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\">Learning Outcomes</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>At the end of this course, participants will;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Have a greater awareness on the issues and pressures on young people to become sexually active and the reasons why early sex happens<br>Understand why early sex is a problem<br>Gain confidence and practical strategies to help & support young people delay sex & be more assertive in saying no to unwanted sex</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\">Overview:</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><em>current youth worker role (link to the youth collective website).&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><em>What I can offer  one off sessions, a series of sessions / workshops, 1-1 work; youth worker training. </em></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><em>overview of the current programme delivered for BH.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><em>Link to IYW. </em></p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Learning Disabilities ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2016-02-25 01:23:00', '2016-05-02 03:06:07', 'ec67dd97-c60d-4fa4-bdc0-60042eb35675'),
 ('25', '64', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Consultancy Work', '<p>Through my consultancy work I am available to plan, deliver and evaluate presentations,&nbsp;seminars, workshops or training courses (either half day or whole day) to practitioners, these include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul><li><strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\"></strong>The influence and impact of pornography and broader \r\nsexualisaion on young people\'s sexual health (including strategies and \r\npractical ways we can respond) </li><li>Sex, Drugs & Alcohol : young people and risk taking</li><li>Behaviour Change = theory into practice - specifically sexual health behaviour change or generic behaviour change</li><li>Pleasure and sexual health promotion: taking a sex positive approach</li><li>R U Ready?: Supporting young people to delay sexual activity until they are ready</li><li>Sex, relationships and the entitlment of young people with learning disabilities </li><li>Unveiling the mask:&nbsp;engaging&nbsp;young men in sex and relationships work</li><li>Supporting young women in building resilience, confidence and assertiveness</li></ul>', 'Education', '<p>I have a specific commitment and interest in ensuring the rights of <strong>young people with learning disabilities to adequate sexual health education </strong>and can provide tailored training on this subject. &nbsp;This work is in conjunction with a very experienced colleague Laura Clark.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>See <a href=\"http://www.lizdeanconsultancy.co.uk/?q=training\">here</a> for more information on this work</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The usual audiences for my courses are; Sexual health promoters / educators, Teachers, GP\'s, Nurses, School nurses, Youth workers,&nbsp; Personal Advisers, Social workers, Health Visitors, Community & Voluntary sector workers and residential staff.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>I can also tailor and deliver any of the above topics to young people directly in or out of school settings. I hold a current full CRB check.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2016-03-28 06:21:34', '2016-04-21 23:43:18', 'ad1d4355-8efc-4479-934b-7c1dac9369f0'),
 ('26', '65', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>I worked as a Senior Sexual Health Promotion Practitioner for the NHS in Brighton & Hove for 12 years. The main areas of my work were: workforce development for practitioners, delivering workshops and seminars, co-ordinating a condom promotion scheme and C-Card scheme, producing resources including a \'Risk workbook\' based on Motivational interviewing, leading on local sexual health media campaigns, chairing local partnership forums and supporting policy & strategy development in the field of teenage pregnancy and sexual health.</p>', '', 'Health', NULL, NULL, 'Health', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2016-03-28 06:32:03', '2016-04-08 22:53:44', '6ecec5bb-4ac1-4380-bb93-56f942172d07'),
 ('27', '66', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>I have recently been working on behalf of the Brighton & Hove Healthy Schools Team and I have developed a teaching pack covering the impact and influence of the media and pornography on young people\'s sexualisation. I developed this resource in partnership with local teachers and in consultation with young people. It was launched and distributed in January 2011 in Brighton & Hove.&nbsp;</p><p><br>The FPA are selling it nationally and all previous participants on the FPA \'Fantasy vs Reality\' Course will be eligible to receive a copy - these will be distributed directly from the FPA. Please contact the FPA for enquiries.<br>See <a href=\"http://www.fpa.org.uk/professionals/publicationsandresources/training-manuals/fantasy-vs-reality-sex-and-relationship-education-resource\">http://www.fpa.org.uk/professi...</a></p><p><br><strong>This resource aims to:</strong><br>Allow teachers and other practitioners to confidently deliver a series of lesson plans / sessions exploring the influence and impact of the media, the internet and pornography on sexual attitudes and the behaviour of young people.<br>&nbsp;<br>The pack contains 5 lesson plans, differentiated for Key Stage 3 (14-15 yr olds) and Key Stage 4 (15-16 yr olds).</p>', '', 'Sex and Relationships', NULL, NULL, 'Teaching Pack Resource', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2016-03-28 06:33:21', '2016-04-08 22:51:11', 'fc6374ff-ede8-4a37-bb21-a0454508d25f'),
 ('28', '67', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 'OLD', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2016-03-28 06:59:02', '2016-05-01 23:20:25', 'b0f6d37b-ceb0-4a5d-85ce-bff60b8a6b6c'),
 ('29', '68', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Contact details to come shortly</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br>\r\n</p>', '', 'Contact Me', NULL, NULL, 'My information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-03-28 07:00:23', '2016-05-17 20:07:08', '44ba2506-6d45-4b17-8e30-fb289fe79775'),
 ('30', '69', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'contact', NULL, '2016-03-28 07:05:19', '2016-05-17 20:07:08', '050eafd5-b5a4-48f2-b2e7-19e02a9e65ff'),
 ('31', '70', 'en_gb', 'test', '', '<p>test</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-03-28 18:07:31', '2016-05-17 20:07:08', '9b895e3e-6fb3-493a-973d-9bf54245b4bc'),
 ('32', '71', 'en_gb', 'test', '', '<p>test</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-03-28 18:08:08', '2016-05-17 20:07:08', 'ec2dbd4a-6fe1-4f23-a944-21027ce1d2ac'),
 ('34', '80', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>I will be in contact with you shortly</p>', '', 'Thanks for contacting me', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2016-05-01 23:19:00', '2016-05-01 23:20:37', '3c6d9658-42a5-49a1-95e1-1f56f0cd155c'),
 ('35', '82', 'en_gb', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>I am a self-employed practitioner in Health Promotion. My main area of interest is in Sexual Health and Relationships work however I have vast experience of working across a variety of areas, including youth work, education and social care covering a range of issues relating to health & well-being, specifically drugs, alcohol and mental health and well-being. I plan and deliver presentations, training courses, workshops and lessons. I also produce teaching resources and health promotion materials, conduct needs assessments and small scale pieces of research.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br>I am based in Sussex, but also work across the UK. I am passionate and committed to Health Promotion and sex and relationships work, specifically the entitlement of young people to high quality objective sex and relationships education. I have been working in the field of Health Promotion, Supporting Behaviour change, Motivational Interviewing and sex and relationships education for 15 years.&nbsp; I am a member of MINT (Motivational Interviewing Network of Trainers)</p>', '', 'Section Heading', NULL, NULL, 'Textbox Heading', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'responsiveLeft', '2016-05-10 19:15:50', '2016-05-10 19:35:02', '156ac22f-123c-4ee8-9316-7480036310e8'),
